<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-11-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-11-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                    <head>No. 292.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right">Received <date calendar="gregorian" type="received-date" when="1880-11-29">November 29,
                            1880</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Evarts</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">State Department, Washington:</hi></p>
                    <p>Gehres’ Alsace case decided in our favor; all penalties and fines remitted
                        both for him and Weill.</p>
                    <closer><signed>WHITE</signed>, <hi rend="italic">Paris.</hi></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>